## Connect Nov 2024

**Deepening SDX Knowledge:** 

By deepening my understanding of SDX, I enhanced my debugging skills, optimized reliability processes, and created a time-saving script for 1JS testing. This foundation helped me address issues faster and contribute tangible improvements to my team.

**Enhancing Reliability for iPad and Mac SDX:** 

My reliability work has focused on critical, production-facing issues. While I am still building in this area, early signs of improvement are evident, and I expect my increasing pace to drive stronger results over time.

**Reducing Testing Efforts for SDX and FHL Hackathon Contribution:** 

This project arose from practical challenges encountered while testing the 1JS app on iPad, where frequent CSS issues demanded rapid adjustments. The manual process of identifying, downloading, and updating 1JS packages in SDX node modules was inefficient, particularly with repeated updates. To address this, I developed a script in JavaScript that automates these tasks, significantly reducing testing time. Key enhancements include optimized file transfer speeds (cut from 80-90 seconds to 10-15 seconds per package), accurate package detection through close SDX collaboration, and parallel processing that reduced update time from 6-8 minutes to under a minute. 
